rComments: Chicken scratch writing. Lectures are all theory (not explained well) and not helpful. No examples of material. Self taught course. Repeats questions for midterm and final. Problem sets were loosely based on lecture material and very difficult to complete.

Professor Moore's lectures are great; he's very intellectual, extremely nice, helpful, and very approachable. His midterms and exams are straightforward but very intellectually stimulating. Really loves teaching this course and helping students out.

Amazing professor! If you work hard, attend lecture, you will do well! Make sure you put a good effort into the problem sets he posts, and if you try your best and go to office hours for help he will lead you to the solution (and yes they are for marks!)! Test and quizzes are very reasonable, if you do the problem sets!
